<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_1129478"><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">引用</div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="font-size: 18pt;" class="bbc_size"><span style="color: red;" class="bbc_color"><strong>以下内容出自B2</strong></span></span></blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div><br><span style="color: maroon;" class="bbc_color"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;" class="bbc_size">蛇龙（Linnorm）</span></strong></span><br>这些强大的蛇形生物被称为蛇龙，他们可能与更加知名的彩色以及金属龙有着某种亲缘关系，但两者之间除了龙类共同的生理结构之外几乎没有任何相似之处。真龙拥有令人难以置信的智能和深谋远虑的计划，而蛇龙只是被他们那永远无法填满的饥饿以及将残忍加诸于他人的欲望所驱使。由于蛇龙这种强烈的意志，使得智取他们变得十分困难，与他们讨价还价更是不明智的选择——在面对这些传说中的猛兽时，最好的选择之一便是拔腿就跑，纯粹且容易施行。但如若无法逃脱的话，接受这高贵的死亡也算是可行的方案。<br>异常强大的蛇龙居住这世界上的偏远地区。此类生物中有个名为法夫尼尔（Fafnheir）的传说，他是所有蛇龙之父，据说是所有蛇龙之中最古老且最强大的存在。法夫尼尔的死亡诅咒会让杀死他的人在精神和肉体的双重层面上不断遭受侵蚀，直至死亡，当被诅咒之人殒命之时，他的尸骸将成为法夫尼尔复生的燃料。<br><br><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">引述: 边栏：建议与规则</div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>蛇龙传说（LINNORM LEGENDS）</strong></span></span><br>像蛇龙这样强大的生物，无论事实准确与否，都很容易诞生属于他们自身的传说。如果你在对蛇龙进行的回忆知识（Recall Knowledge）检定中得到大失败的结果，就会得到类似于通过在打出致命一击之时闭眼就可以免遭蛇龙的死亡诅咒，或者用有毒的橡树摩擦身体可以避开蛇龙的目光这样的信息。</blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div><br><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">引述: 边栏：额外学识</div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>蛇龙幼崽（NEWBORN LINNORMS）</strong></span></span><br>几乎所有蛇龙都独自生活；就连蛇龙的同类自身也不能忍受彼此的存在。这种生物甚至不会为了繁殖而彼此接触；取而代之的是，雌性蛇龙会在偏远地区产下龙蛋，当游荡的雄性蛇龙发现之后会让龙蛋受精并找个合适的地方将其孵化。新生蛇龙的体格区间从成年的鳄鱼到发育完全的公牛均有可能，而且他们的发育速度很快。即便是一头幼年蛇龙也强大到可以对小型定居点造成严重的破坏——不过大多数蛇龙不敢如此大肆掠食，因为他们害怕这么做会招致此区域内其他更加庞大的蛇龙的愤怒。<br><br><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>与第一世界的关系（FIRST WORLD CONNECTIONS）</strong></span></span><br>蛇龙与第一世界——精类原本的家园——有着深厚的联系。尽管蛇龙会不假思索地吞下侏儒或者其他精类，但他们确实会对强大的原能魔法使用者报以非比寻常的尊敬。根据常识，能够恐吓蛇龙的唯一方法就是提醒他自然之力远比蛇龙本身更加强大。</blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div><br><div class="quoteheader"><div class="topslice_quote">引述: 边栏：关联生物</div></div><blockquote class="bbc_standard_quote"><span style="color: purple;" class="bbc_color"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>稀有蛇龙（RARER LINNORMS）</strong></span></span><br>尽管本书以及第一本怪物图鉴（Bestiary）中已经刊载了大多数蛇龙，但其他蛇龙也是存在的，他们主要存在于情况在第一世界的偏远地区。这可能是因为这些稀有的蛇龙认为主物质位面对他们的力量带来了过多的约束。</blockquote><div class="quotefooter"><div class="botslice_quote"></div></div><br><span style="font-size: 12pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>原文</strong></span><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i>原文</i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Linnorm<br>The powerful, serpentine beings known as linnorms may be distantly related to the more well-known chromatic and metallic dragons, but their draconic physiologies are where any such similarities end. Whereas true dragons boast incredible intellectual capabilities and far-reaching plans, linnorms are driven only by their insatiable hunger and desire to inflict cruelty on others. Linnorms are exceptionally difficult to outwit due to their strong wills, and it’s not wise to try bargaining with them—when faced with one of these legendary beasts, one’s best option is flight, pure and simple. Failing that, a noble death is a viable back-up plan.<br>Extremely powerful linnorms dwell in remote parts of the world. One such creature is the legendary Fafnheir, the Father of All Linnorms, said to be the oldest and mightiest linnorm of them all. Fafnheir’s death curse causes anyone who would slay him to slowly erode away physically and mentally until they die, at which point the cursed victim’s body fuels Fafnheir’s resurrection.<br><br>LINNORM LEGENDS<br>Creatures as powerful as linnorms tend to spawn stories of their own, accurate or not. Critical failure on a check to Recall Knowledge on linnorms might suggest that you can avoid a linnorm’s death curse by closing your eyes as you deliver the fatal blow, or that rubbing poison oak on yourself can ward off a linnorm’s attention.<br><br>NEWBORN LINNORMS<br>Almost all linnorms lead solitary lives; they are too reprehensible for even their own kind to tolerate for any length of time. Most species do not even meet to reproduce; rather, female linnorms usually deposit a solitary egg in a remote location, which a wandering male linnorm then fertilizes and places in a nook suitable for incubation. Newborn linnorms range in size from that of adult crocodiles to full-grown bulls, and their growth is rapid. Even a juvenile linnorm is strong enough to wreak havoc on a small settlement—though most don’t dare to commit such audacious pillaging, for fear of evoking the anger of another, larger linnorm in the area.<br><br>FIRST WORLD CONNECTIONS<br>Linnorms have a deep connection to the First World, the primordial home of the fey. While linnorms typically won’t think twice before devouring a gnome or other fey, they do have an unusual respect for wielders of powerful primal magic. The only way to cow a linnorm, according to common wisdom, is to remind it that there are forces of nature even stronger than itself.<br><br>RARER LINNORMS<br>While the linnorms presented here and in the first Bestiary constitute the majority of these creatures, others exist, particularly in the remote regions of the First World. It may be that these rare linnorms simply find the Material Plane too constraining for their might！<br></div></div></div></div>
</div>
</div>
